        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 8:14PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 814 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Valier, or 18 miles south of Cut Bank, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Valier.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
